ingredientsDesc:
4.1 Osteocalcin Calibrator 0: BSA-borate buffer contains 0.2% sodium azide as a preservative.
4.2 Osteocalcin Calibrator: Bovine osteocalcin calibrator, at a normal concentration of 25 ng/ml, is diluted in BSA-borate buffer containing 0.1% sodium azide. The exact concentration value of the calibrator is assigned according to each lot. This calibrator is of bovine bone origin and has been highly purified by HPLC.
4.3 Osteocalcin Antiserum: Rabbit anti-osteocalcin serum is diluted in BSA-borate buffer containing 0.5% sodium azide.
4.4 125I Osteocalcin: Bovine osteocalcin is labeled with iodine-125 and diluted in BSA-borate buffer containing 0.5% sodium azide.
4.5 Precipitating Complex (GAR-PPT): Normal rabbit serum, pre-precipitated with goat anti-rabbit serum and polyethylene glycol (PEG), is diluted in BSA-borate buffer with 0.1% sodium azide and other preservatives added.
